41
00:03:23,365 --> 00:03:27,031
Next up: The Six Key Technologies Powering 6G.

42
00:03:27,031 --> 00:03:29,663
6G isn't a single technology.

43
00:03:29,663 --> 00:03:33,665
It's a convergence of six breakthrough technologies working together.

44
00:03:33,665 --> 00:03:37,752
Technology 1: Terahertz (THz) Communication.

45
00:03:37,752 --> 00:03:46,923
THz communication uses frequencies between 0.1 and 10 THz - far above the millimeter-wave bands used by 5G.

46
00:03:46,923 --> 00:03:51,502
This is the technology that enables the extreme speeds of 6G.

47
00:03:51,502 --> 00:03:57,620
Why THz Matters: Massive bandwidth available (hundreds of GHz of contiguous spectrum).

48
00:03:57,620 --> 00:04:01,021
Enables 1 Tbps theoretical speeds.

49
00:04:01,021 --> 00:04:06,430
Short range means extreme spatial reuse (zero interference between rooms).

50
00:04:06,430 --> 00:04:09,819
2025-2026 Breakthroughs:

51
00:04:09,819 --> 00:04:24,459
October 2025: e& (UAE telecom) and NYU Abu Dhabi achieved 145 Gbps in a THz wireless pilot - the fastest THz transmission ever recorded in a real-world setting.

52
00:04:24,459 --> 00:04:32,932
This used frequencies above 100 GHz and demonstrated that THz communication is moving from theory to practice.

53
00:04:32,932 --> 00:04:45,552
November 2025: Researchers published a portable 220 GHz ISAC device in Nature Communications - combining THz communication with sensing in a single handheld device.

54
00:04:45,552 --> 00:04:50,733
This is significant because THz previously required room-sized equipment.

55
00:04:50,733 --> 00:04:53,762
Technology 2: AI-Native Networks.

56
00:04:53,762 --> 00:04:56,079
This is perhaps the most important shift.

57
00:04:56,079 --> 00:05:01,572
In 5G, AI optimizes existing protocols designed by humans.

58
00:05:01,572 --> 00:05:05,346
In 6G, AI designs the protocols themselves.

59
00:05:05,346 --> 00:05:07,125
What the major companies are doing:

60
00:05:07,125 --> 00:05:19,589
Nokia Bell Labs: Developing an AI/ML-defined air interface where the physical layer encoding and decoding is performed by neural networks instead of traditional signal processing.

61
00:05:19,589 --> 00:05:33,724
Samsung: Published 6G White Paper v2 (February 2025) detailing AI at Layer 1 (noise reduction, channel estimation) and Layer 2 (resource allocation, scheduling).

62
00:05:33,724 --> 00:05:42,474
Ericsson: Pushing for AI-native design in 3GPP Release 21, their roadmap for "AI as a protocol layer".

63
00:05:42,474 --> 00:05:47,750
Technology 3: Reconfigurable Intelligent Surfaces (RIS).

64
00:05:47,750 --> 00:06:00,238
RIS are "programmable walls" - metasurfaces with thousands of tiny elements that can be electronically controlled to reflect, refract, or absorb radio signals in specific directions.

65
00:06:00,238 --> 00:06:11,632
March 2025 Breakthrough: Researchers at the University of Manchester demonstrated graphene-based RIS that can dynamically switch between reflecting and absorbing THz signals.

66
00:06:11,632 --> 00:06:18,880
Graphene's unique properties allow RIS panels to operate at THz frequencies - essential for 6G.

67
00:06:18,880 --> 00:06:22,918
Previous RIS designs only worked at lower frequencies.

68
00:06:22,918 --> 00:06:27,005
Technology 4: Non-Terrestrial Networks (NTN).

69
00:06:27,005 --> 00:06:34,962
6G aims for true global coverage by integrating space, air, and ground networks into a unified system.

70
00:06:34,962 --> 00:06:41,776
Recent Development: China Mobile launched a 6G test satellite to validate space-ground integration.

71
00:06:41,776 --> 00:06:55,971
South Korea's K-Network 2030 program specifically targets NTN as a national priority, and the European Space Agency (ESA) has partnered with 6G-ANNA for satellite-terrestrial convergence research.

72
00:06:55,971 --> 00:07:01,019
Technology 5: Integrated Sensing and Communication (ISAC).

73
00:07:01,019 --> 00:07:06,067
ISAC turns the entire 6G network into a massive sensor network.

74
00:07:06,067 --> 00:07:15,310
The same signals used for communication also sense the environment - detecting objects, measuring distances, and tracking movement with centimeter precision.

75
00:07:15,310 --> 00:07:22,185
Applications for developers: Indoor positioning with cm-level accuracy (no GPS needed).

76
00:07:22,185 --> 00:07:25,887
Autonomous vehicle sensing via network infrastructure.

77
00:07:25,887 --> 00:07:28,760
Gesture-based interfaces without cameras.

78
00:07:28,760 --> 00:07:32,702
Health monitoring through radio signals (breathing, heart rate).

79
00:07:32,702 --> 00:07:35,478
Smart home without dedicated sensors.

80
00:07:35,478 --> 00:07:38,627
Technology 6: Semantic Communication.

81
00:07:38,627 --> 00:07:42,582
This might be the most mind-bending technology in 6G.

82
00:07:42,582 --> 00:07:49,409
Instead of transmitting the exact bits of data, semantic communication transmits the meaning of the data.

83
00:07:49,409 --> 00:07:53,796
This fundamentally changes how developers think about data transmission.

84
00:07:53,796 --> 00:07:58,423
Instead of optimizing for bit rates, you optimize for meaning preservation.

85
00:07:58,423 --> 00:08:01,464
Let's explore Timeline and Standardization.

