116
00:10:20,142 --> 00:10:22,918
India learned from its 5G experience.

117
00:10:22,918 --> 00:10:28,759
With 5G, India was a late adopter but achieved the world's fastest rollout once it began.

118
00:10:28,759 --> 00:10:33,171
For 6G, India wants to be a creator, not just a consumer.

119
00:10:33,171 --> 00:10:35,779
Bharat 6G Vision Document.

120
00:10:35,779 --> 00:10:48,399
In March 2023, the Indian government released the Bharat 6G Vision Document, setting an ambitious target: India should own 10% of global 6G intellectual property.

121
00:10:48,399 --> 00:10:54,709
Given that India currently holds less than 1% of 5G patents, this is a massive leap.

122
00:10:54,709 --> 00:10:55,935
Key Developments.

123
00:10:55,935 --> 00:11:06,884
Bharat 6G Alliance (B6GA): Launched with 80+ member organizations including telecom operators, startups, academic institutions, and government bodies.

124
00:11:06,884 --> 00:11:13,651
The alliance coordinates India's 6G research efforts and represents India in international forums.

125
00:11:13,651 --> 00:11:27,521
TSDSI Partnership (July 2025): The Telecommunications Standards Development Society, India (TSDSI) formally partnered with B6GA to ensure India's voice in 3GPP standardization.

126
00:11:27,521 --> 00:11:34,336
TSDSI has already contributed to 5G standards and aims to play a larger role in 6G.

127
00:11:34,336 --> 00:11:42,053
International MoUs: India has signed bilateral agreements with 8 countries and organizations for 6G collaboration.

128
00:11:42,053 --> 00:11:51,860
The US-India partnership and the Finland collaboration (home of Nokia and 6G Flagship program at University of Oulu) are particularly significant.

129
00:11:51,860 --> 00:12:02,089
Funding: The government has funded 115 projects worth Rs. 310.6 Crore (~$37M) across research institutions.

130
00:12:02,089 --> 00:12:06,332
While this is modest compared to China or the US, it's a starting point.

131
00:12:06,332 --> 00:12:12,690
The 100 5G labs established across institutions serve as the testing ground for 6G research.

132
00:12:12,690 --> 00:12:24,493
IIT Research: Multiple IITs have established dedicated 6G research facilities: IIT Madras: 6G THz Testbed for testing sub-THz communication.

133
00:12:24,493 --> 00:12:29,577
IIT Guwahati: THz antenna design and characterization.

134
00:12:29,577 --> 00:12:35,034
IIT Patna: 6G communication algorithms and protocols.

135
00:12:35,034 --> 00:12:40,142
IIIT Bangalore: AI/ML for next-generation wireless networks.

136
00:12:40,142 --> 00:12:42,678
India's 5G Foundation.

137
00:12:42,678 --> 00:12:47,726
India's rapid 5G deployment gives it a strong foundation for 6G:

138
00:12:47,726 --> 00:12:55,887
Jio and Airtel have deployed 5G in 779 and 783 districts respectively.

139
00:12:55,887 --> 00:12:59,240
Over 460,000 base stations installed.

140
00:12:59,240 --> 00:13:06,764
200+ million 5G subscribers (Jio alone - world's largest 5G network by users).

141
00:13:06,764 --> 00:13:13,207
The fastest 5G rollout in telecom history (18 months to nationwide coverage).

142
00:13:13,207 --> 00:13:21,728
Jio's AirFiber: 7.4 million users - world's largest Fixed Wireless Access (FWA) deployment.

143
00:13:21,728 --> 00:13:28,784
This infrastructure, expertise, and subscriber base positions India to be an early 6G adopter.

144
00:13:28,784 --> 00:13:31,572
Moving on to What 6G Enables for Developers.

145
00:13:31,572 --> 00:13:37,618
6G opens up application categories that are literally impossible with current technology.

146
00:13:37,618 --> 00:13:42,113
Ericsson has identified seven key use case families for 6G:

147
00:13:42,113 --> 00:13:43,699
Use Case Deep Dives.

148
00:13:43,699 --> 00:13:51,079
Holographic Communication: Imagine a video call where the person appears as a full 3D hologram in your room.

149
00:13:51,079 --> 00:13:57,966
This requires streaming 3D volumetric data at 4.32 Tbps (uncompressed).

150
00:13:57,966 --> 00:14:04,372
Even with compression, this needs sustained speeds of 100+ Gbps with sub-millisecond latency.

151
00:14:04,372 --> 00:14:06,740
Only 6G can deliver this.

152
00:14:06,740 --> 00:14:15,791
Massive Digital Twins: A digital twin of Mumbai - every building, vehicle, person, utility pipe - updated in real-time.

153
00:14:15,791 --> 00:14:22,870
This requires millions of sensors per square kilometer feeding data to an AI-powered digital replica.

154
00:14:22,870 --> 00:14:28,267
City planners could simulate the impact of a new metro line before laying a single track.

155
00:14:28,274 --> 00:14:34,750
Brain-Computer Interfaces: The human brain generates about 100 Gbps of neural data.

156
00:14:34,750 --> 00:14:44,546
To create a real-time brain-computer interface (think: controlling a computer with your thoughts), you need to transmit and process this data with near-zero latency.

157
00:14:44,546 --> 00:14:50,687
6G's combination of extreme speed and ultra-low latency makes this feasible for the first time.

158
00:14:50,687 --> 00:14:58,007
Autonomous Vehicle V2X: Vehicles need to share sensor data with each other and the infrastructure in real-time.

159
00:14:58,007 --> 00:15:04,149
At highway speeds, a car travels 3 cm in 0.1ms.

160
00:15:04,149 --> 00:15:11,865
6G's sub-0.1ms latency means vehicles can react to each other's data before they physically move.

